                "display_name": "ZeroWorks"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1485937603,
            "creation_date": 1485602743,
            "body": "<p>I solved it setting page mode followin Marc Balmer's example, but have to send feed for 24*2 dots (line height double density) to get it working: So after every slice of data send command <code>ESC J n<\/code> bytes <code>{27, 74, 48}<\/code>. And finally got it!<\/p>\n\n<p>Hope it helps!<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://reference.epson-biz.com/modules/ref_escpos/index.php?content_id=15\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Reference (must be logged)<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 41909223,
            "question_id": 21192888,
            "last_edit_date": 1485937603
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e0243edcd49f8deaeedcbdd68246e1fe?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 4217876,
                "user_type": "unregistered",
                "user_id": 3453470,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3453470/kutar",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "kutar"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1396177264,
            "creation_date": 1395614004,
            "body": "<p>Try sending ESC/POS command (0x1B, '3', 24) prior to printing. This sets the line spacing to 24 dots rather than the default of 30.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 22598014,
            "question_id": 21192888,
            "last_edit_date": 1396177264
        },
        {
